topic.title: LBI Interface

body.note: This content was sourced from PMC-2140577 - SrPB Telecom System Block Engineering Document Issue 1.00
body.p: Switchtec feaures a l16 features a 16-bit wide asynchronous local bus interface for connecting to external SRAM memory. This interface is able to address up to four devices and up to 16 MB per device.
The memory controller supports the local bus interface. It has four chip selects for local bus interface. Each chip select supports one 16 MB space.

When the local bus is configured in 16-bit data mode, LBI_A[23:1] are at the 16-bit address boundary. LBI_A[23:1] are used to address a 16 MB space per chip select signal, since every address is a 16-bit data access. LBI_A[0] is a Lower Byte Enable (LBI_BYTENB[0]) to select LBI_DATA[7:0], and LBI_BYTENB[1] is an Upper Byte Enable to control DATA[15:8].

During device reset, LBI_A[23:0], LBI_DATA[15:0], LBI_OEB, LBI_WEB, and LBI_CEB[3:0] will be tri-stated. If there is another device on the board that wants to control the SRAM on the local bus, it can assert the SRAM RESETB pin and take over the local bus control.
